ls; celestial navigation; polyhedra; stereographic projection; and more. He conveys the sheer beauty of spherical trigonometry, providing readers with a new appreciation of its elegant proofs and often surprising conclusions. Heavenly Mathematics is illustrated throughout with stunning historical images and informative drawings and diagrams. This unique compendium also features easy-to-use appendixes as well as exercises that originally appeared in textbooks from the eighteenth to the early twentieth centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMATHEMATICSvGeometryvGeneral. 0aMATHEMATICSvTrigonometry. 0aSpherical trigonometry. 0aTrigonometry. 7aMATHEMATICS / History & Philosophy.2bisacsh  aAbū 'l-Wafā.  aAbū Mahmūd al-Khujandī.  aAbū Nasr Mansūr ibn 'Alī ibn 'Irāq.  aAbū Sahl al-Kūhī.  aAlbert Girard.  aB. M. Brown.  aCesàro method.  aChristopher Columbus.  aClaudius Ptolemy.  aEarth.  aElements.  aGeorg Rheticus.  aGiuseppe Cesàro.  aHipparchus of Rhodes.  aIslam.  aIslamic religious rituals.  aJohn Harrison.  aJohn Napier.  aLaw of Cosines.  aLaw of Sines.  aLeonhard Euler.  aMathematical Collection.  aMecca.  aMenelaus of Alexandria.  aMenelaus's Theorem.  aMoon.  aNapier's Rules.  aOpus palatinum.  aPlanisphere.  aPtolemy.  aPythagorean Theorem.  aRule of Four Quantities.  aSphaerica.  aSun.  aacute-angled triangle.  aangle.  aarea.  aastrolabe.  aastronomical triangle.  aastronomy.  acartography.  acelestial motion.  acelestial sphere.  achronometer.  aclassical Greece.  adead reckoning.  aecliptic.  aequatorial coordinates.  ageography.  alocality principle.  alogarithms.  amarteloio.  amathematics.  amethod of Saint Hilaire.  anavigation.  aoblique triangle.  apentagramma mirificum.  aplan